  "prompt": "Can you be a pilot if you wear glasses?",
  "response": "Yes, you can be a pilot if you wear glasses. Many pilots wear corrective lenses, including glasses and contact lenses, to meet the vision requirements set by aviation authorities. However, there are specific vision standards that must be met, which can vary by country and the type of pilot certification being sought. \n\nTypically, a first-class medical certificate (required for airline transport pilots) may have stricter vision requirements than a second-class or third-class medical certificate. A comprehensive eye exam is usually required to determine if your vision meets the necessary standards. It's important to consult with an aviation medical examiner to ensure you meet all the requirements before pursuing your pilot's license.",
